xts of religion and modern state formation. While these changes are typically explained in terms of secularization of the state and the birth of rational modern man, the life and afterlives of Sayyid Fadl—which take us from eighteenth- and nineteenth-century Indian Ocean worlds to twenty-first century cyberspace—offer a more open-ended global history of sovereignty and a more capacious conception of life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aIslam and politicszIndian Ocean RegionxHistory. 0aMoplahszIndiazMalabarvBiography. 0aPolitical activistszIndiazMalabarvBiography. 0aSovereigntyxReligious aspectsxIslam. 0aSufiszIndiazMalabarvBiography. 7aHISTORY / Asia / India & South Asia.2bisacsh  aBritish Empire.  aHadhramawt.  aIndian Ocean.  aMalabar.  aMiddle East.  aOttoman Empire.  aSayyid Fadl Ibn Alawi.  aSouth Asia.  aSovereignty.  aSufism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020z9783110704525oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311069228040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150360964840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503609648423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503609648.jpg  a978-3-11-069228-0  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070473-0  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020